1
00:00:31,490 --> 00:00:32,799
Cambodia.

2
00:00:33,984 --> 00:00:36,605
To many Westerners,
it seemed a paradise.

3
00:00:36,802 --> 00:00:39,832
Another world, a secret world.

4
00:00:40,127 --> 00:00:43,902
But the war in neighboring
Vietnam burst its borders...

5
00:00:44,094 --> 00:00:47,476
...and the fighting soon spread
to neutral Cambodia.

6
00:00:48,383 --> 00:00:51,448
In 1973, I went to cover
this sideshow struggle...

7
00:00:51,647 --> 00:00:54,614
...as foreign correspondent
of The New York Times.

8
00:00:54,977 --> 00:00:57,628
It was there, amidst the fighting...

9
00:00:57,826 --> 00:01:01,019
...between government troops
and the Khmer Rouge guerrillas...

10
00:01:01,215 --> 00:01:04,662
...that I met my guide
and interpreter, Dith Pran...

11
00:01:04,863 --> 00:01:07,733
...a man who was to change my life...

12
00:01:07,936 --> 00:01:10,780
...in a country that I grew to love
and pity.

13
00:01:19,616 --> 00:01:22,300
So here we go
with Voice of America...

14
00:01:22,495 --> 00:01:24,405
...news for Southeast Asia.

15
00:01:24,608 --> 00:01:28,565
It's 6:45 and a partly cloudy
morning here.

16
00:01:28,764 --> 00:01:30,936
Clouds too in Washington.

17
00:01:31,132 --> 00:01:34,746
President Nixon announced he'll
address the nation on Watergate...

18
00:01:34,941 --> 00:01:36,731
...within the next few days.

19
00:01:36,924 --> 00:01:39,445
The speech will be Nixon's
first since May.

20
00:01:41,213 --> 00:01:45,076
The scandal has caused resignations
and paralyzed the White House staff.

21
00:01:45,279 --> 00:01:48,727
It has also led to intense
confrontation and perhaps...

22
00:01:48,924 --> 00:01:51,675
...a constitutional crisis
with Senate investigators...

23
00:01:51,871 --> 00:01:54,389
...and a special
Watergate prosecutor.

24
00:01:54,589 --> 00:01:57,819
The speech was announced
after the Gallup Poll disclosed...

25
00:01:58,013 --> 00:02:01,722
...that Mr. Nixon's popularity
had fallen to the lowest point...

26
00:02:01,918 --> 00:02:04,602
...for an American President
in 20 years.

27
00:02:15,931 --> 00:02:18,579
A Supreme Court judge,
William O. Douglas...

28
00:02:18,778 --> 00:02:21,627
...has ruled against an appeal
by the Administration...

29
00:02:21,820 --> 00:02:23,412
...for a stay of the injunction...

30
00:02:23,610 --> 00:02:26,960
...on further U.S. Bombing
missions in Cambodia.

31
00:02:27,164 --> 00:02:30,034
Congress has already ruled
these bombings illegal...

32
00:02:30,237 --> 00:02:34,328
...and they should cease in one
week's time on August the 15th.

33
00:02:54,908 --> 00:02:56,815
Let's go, Sarun!
To the hospital!

34
00:03:15,004 --> 00:03:17,042
Information. Information.

35
00:03:17,244 --> 00:03:21,977
Air Cambodia regret delays of arrival
of flight number 125...

36
00:03:22,171 --> 00:03:25,650
...from Bangkok because
of bad weather.

37
00:03:46,201 --> 00:03:48,242
Mister, you want taxi?

38
00:03:48,440 --> 00:03:50,613
Mister, you want taxi?
Good taxi.

39
00:04:17,018 --> 00:04:19,952
Shut the fucking blinds, will you?

40
00:04:24,183 --> 00:04:25,774
What's all this shit?

41
00:04:28,694 --> 00:04:30,035
I'm sorry.

42
00:04:30,807 --> 00:04:34,038
I thought you were the houseboy.
I was developing some film.

43
00:04:34,519 --> 00:04:37,934
If you're gonna yell, I'll come back.
I'm not feeling good.

44
00:04:38,135 --> 00:04:40,471
Don't want to yell.
I want to be in a good mood.

45
00:04:40,663 --> 00:04:43,477
The plane was late, no car.
I had to take a taxi here.

46
00:04:43,671 --> 00:04:45,941
All I want to do is work.
I got you.

47
00:04:55,512 --> 00:04:57,748
What the fuck is that on your head?

48
00:05:00,150 --> 00:05:03,497
It's a sanitary napkin.
I had it soaked in ice.

49
00:05:05,078 --> 00:05:07,633
Syd Schanberg.
Is Pran there?

50
00:05:09,431 --> 00:05:11,469
No, I just came from the airport.

51
00:05:12,373 --> 00:05:15,241
Well, if he comes in,
would you tell him I'm here?

52
00:05:15,572 --> 00:05:17,963
I'll be at the Caf Central, tell him.

53
00:05:18,419 --> 00:05:19,369
Thanks a lot.

54
00:05:36,503 --> 00:05:37,644
What do you want to eat?

55
00:05:39,668 --> 00:05:40,496
Want some eggs?

56
00:05:40,691 --> 00:05:44,073
I can't. Somebody told me they faint
with fright when you cook them.

57
00:05:44,273 --> 00:05:46,413
- What do you want to eat?
- What are you having?

58
00:05:46,611 --> 00:05:48,107
I'm having a caf complet.

59
00:05:48,722 --> 00:05:50,994
I'll have that. And some aspirin.

60
00:05:58,419 --> 00:06:01,837
Anything I eat has got to be
absolutely dead.

61
00:06:02,036 --> 00:06:03,855
That's why I can never eat an oyster.

62
00:06:04,436 --> 00:06:07,250
I read somewhere that they put...

63
00:06:09,491 --> 00:06:12,973
...that lemon juice on them
just to stun them. You know?

64
00:06:13,169 --> 00:06:14,284
What's the difference?

65
00:06:15,698 --> 00:06:19,953
An unconscious oyster's just as
horrible as the fucker wide awake...

66
00:06:33,683 --> 00:06:35,984
- My God! Look at this.
- Did you see that?

67
00:06:36,178 --> 00:06:37,454
What was it? A rocket?

68
00:06:37,651 --> 00:06:40,236
I don't know.
I saw a guy on a motorbike.

69
00:06:48,754 --> 00:06:50,132
I've been looking for you.

70
00:06:50,325 --> 00:06:51,818
I left a message for you.

71
00:06:52,018 --> 00:06:53,956
I didn't get it. I took a cab.

72
00:06:54,161 --> 00:06:56,977
- There is a big accident right now.
- What?

73
00:06:57,170 --> 00:07:00,400
I think U.S. Drop many big bombs
on little city.

74
00:07:00,879 --> 00:07:03,782
- U.S. Bombs? You're sure?
- I think many dead.

75
00:07:03,985 --> 00:07:06,372
- Does anybody else know about it?
- Nothing at all.

76
00:07:07,314 --> 00:07:08,327
We're going.

77
00:07:08,592 --> 00:07:10,982
Not possible right now, Sydney.
Too dangerous.

78
00:07:38,191 --> 00:07:39,916
Where you going, Schanberg?

79
00:07:41,425 --> 00:07:42,798
Neak Luong.

80
00:07:42,990 --> 00:07:44,202
Neak Luong's closed.

81
00:07:44,399 --> 00:07:48,010
Don't give me that, Reeves.
You got nothing to say about this.

82
00:07:48,207 --> 00:07:51,556
I got a right to go wherever I like
in this sad little country.

83
00:07:51,758 --> 00:07:56,461
That's the law. You impede me, you're
breaking the Cooper/Church Amendment!

84
00:07:56,655 --> 00:07:59,406
Well, up the Cooper/Church
Amendment's ass!

85
00:08:01,872 --> 00:08:02,981
Let's go!

86
00:08:13,485 --> 00:08:15,492
So how can I help you, Mr. Schanberg?

87
00:08:19,375 --> 00:08:24,079
I'm looking for information on why
my airplane was delayed this morning.

88
00:08:25,358 --> 00:08:27,462
- Your plane was delayed?
- That's right.

89
00:08:27,664 --> 00:08:30,826
I don't know. Maybe it's
bad weather. Your flight's...

90
00:08:31,025 --> 00:08:32,995
You don't know anything about it?

91
00:08:33,707 --> 00:08:34,722
No, I don't.

92
00:08:35,182 --> 00:08:36,129
All right.

93
00:08:37,902 --> 00:08:40,290
Then I'd like you
to listen to something...

94
00:08:40,494 --> 00:08:42,436
...and then I'd like a comment.

95
00:08:42,798 --> 00:08:46,341
This morning, for reasons beyond
anybody's control...

96
00:08:46,540 --> 00:08:50,471
...I spend two hours in Bangkok
staring at a seat belt sign.

97
00:08:50,669 --> 00:08:52,164
Meanwhile, my sources tell me...

98
00:08:52,366 --> 00:08:56,008
...two Army helicopters are landing
here, just across the airfield.

99
00:08:56,558 --> 00:08:59,688
Half the ambulances in Phnom Penh
are waiting there to meet them.

100
00:09:00,076 --> 00:09:04,068
And now there's a rumor that
the U.S. Air Force dropped a bomb...

101
00:09:04,267 --> 00:09:06,089
...or several bombs, on Neak Luong.

102
00:09:06,283 --> 00:09:09,317
That's a rumor, and I'm not gonna
comment on a rumor.

103
00:09:09,516 --> 00:09:13,410
I just want to know if that's the
reason why my airplane was delayed!

104
00:09:17,133 --> 00:09:18,061
No comment.

105
00:09:18,989 --> 00:09:20,103
How many killed?

106
00:09:23,049 --> 00:09:24,295
How many wounded?

107
00:09:29,643 --> 00:09:32,261
Thank you for your cooperation,
Major Reeves.

108
00:09:34,443 --> 00:09:38,503
When I scrape this story out, I will
no doubt be quoting you in full!

109
00:10:19,625 --> 00:10:20,705
I'm sorry.

110
00:10:21,258 --> 00:10:23,144
This is just not good enough.

111
00:10:23,337 --> 00:10:25,247
This is a big story...

112
00:10:25,449 --> 00:10:29,508
...a major story, you understand that?
We've got to get down there!

113
00:10:29,705 --> 00:10:31,713
- I know, but...
- I don't want to hear "no"!

114
00:10:31,914 --> 00:10:33,823
I want to get down that river!

115
00:10:34,025 --> 00:10:35,685
We should be down there now!

116
00:10:47,562 --> 00:10:48,835
I'll be here.

117
00:10:51,304 --> 00:10:52,735
Good night, Sydney.

118
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:03,168
- Messages?
- No, sir.

119
00:11:03,686 --> 00:11:04,637
No, sir.

120
00:11:06,599 --> 00:11:09,700
I'd talk, but it's been
a heavy day and I've got to go.

121
00:11:09,895 --> 00:11:12,264
Let's get together again soon, okay?

122
00:11:12,455 --> 00:11:13,764
- Bob?
- See you.

123
00:11:14,215 --> 00:11:15,142
Bob?

124
00:11:16,199 --> 00:11:18,107
Hello, Sydney. Good night, Sydney.

125
00:11:18,309 --> 00:11:21,378
- Listen, I can't talk with you.
- You can talk to me.

126
00:11:21,577 --> 00:11:24,423
The embassy is jittery.
Get information from a press officer.

127
00:11:24,615 --> 00:11:26,819
Let's not start insulting each other.

128
00:11:29,028 --> 00:11:30,588
Good night, Sydney.

129
00:11:31,462 --> 00:11:32,870
All right, good night.

130
00:11:38,118 --> 00:11:39,908
You've heard of pilot error?

131
00:11:40,104 --> 00:11:41,531
Computer malfunction?

132
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:43,780
They screwed up on the coordinates.

133
00:11:43,974 --> 00:11:47,588
A single B-52 dropped
its entire load on Neak Luong.

134
00:11:49,255 --> 00:11:51,842
There's a homing beacon
in the middle of the town.

135
00:11:53,379 --> 00:11:55,291
- Casualties?
- You'll be briefed tomorrow.

136
00:11:55,491 --> 00:12:00,002
We estimate 55 military,
something like 35 civilians.

137
00:12:01,382 --> 00:12:02,558
How many?

138
00:12:04,870 --> 00:12:07,554
I hear it's in the hundreds.
Don't quote me on that.

139
00:12:07,749 --> 00:12:10,881
Will there be a dreadful bloodbath

140
00:12:11,078 --> 00:12:14,047
When the Khmer Rouge hit the town?

141
00:12:14,502 --> 00:12:17,086
Will there be a dreadful bloodbath...?

142
00:12:19,684 --> 00:12:21,788
Beer! We haven't had this
for four weeks.

143
00:12:22,180 --> 00:12:24,003
New York Times probably
had it flown in.

144
00:12:24,579 --> 00:12:27,843
- They keep it in their suite.
- We got a cellar. Don't you know?

145
00:12:28,037 --> 00:12:30,404
Americans take themselves so seriously.

146
00:12:30,596 --> 00:12:35,201
Don't be hard on the man. He's just
trying to get to the top of the heap.

147
00:12:35,397 --> 00:12:38,843
We'll just have to pay more to get
our telexes to the top of the heap.

148
00:12:39,046 --> 00:12:41,466
The man has just bought you a beer.
Now drink up.

149
00:12:41,669 --> 00:12:42,682
- Cheers.
- Cheers, Syd.

150
00:12:42,883 --> 00:12:44,792
- Enjoy it.
- Off to see the telex operator?

151
00:12:44,997 --> 00:12:47,297
- New York Times goes to bed early.
- Sure!

152
00:12:48,964 --> 00:12:51,613
Khmer Rouge in the sunset

153
00:12:52,963 --> 00:12:55,298
The Yanks all at sea...

154
00:12:58,978 --> 00:13:00,986
- All right?
- Very possible.

155
00:13:02,118 --> 00:13:03,521
Let's go then!

156
00:13:11,202 --> 00:13:12,630
This is good work.

157
00:13:47,777 --> 00:13:49,273
- How much?
- Hundred fifty.

158
00:13:56,322 --> 00:13:57,268
One hundred!

159
00:14:03,071 --> 00:14:04,479
- All right?
- All right.

160
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,626
Nice going, Pran.

161
00:15:09,983 --> 00:15:12,535
- What is he saying?
- He wants you to look at his family.

162
00:15:12,731 --> 00:15:16,989
To take a photograph and help him
because his child was wounded.

163
00:15:42,429 --> 00:15:44,436
Tell me what she's saying.

164
00:15:46,650 --> 00:15:48,080
She needs help.

165
00:15:51,868 --> 00:15:54,391
Her shop was destroyed last night.

166
00:15:55,548 --> 00:15:56,925
Her husband killed.

167
00:15:57,118 --> 00:15:58,292
How many bombs?

168
00:16:00,158 --> 00:16:01,368
She doesn't know.

169
00:16:02,429 --> 00:16:04,370
Does she know where the hospital is?

170
00:16:06,076 --> 00:16:07,352
"Just over there."

171
00:16:13,405 --> 00:16:15,542
She wants to know,
"Did someone arrest the pilot?"

172
00:16:18,076 --> 00:16:20,757
Mister, you wanna buy?
Mister, you wanna buy?

173
00:16:21,116 --> 00:16:24,213
- One dollar? You wanna buy?
- I'm out of film. I'm sorry.

174
00:16:25,339 --> 00:16:28,183
Ask her how many kids she's got
in her family.

175
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:30,231
"Five."

176
00:16:30,682 --> 00:16:33,016
Her husband was killed already.

177
00:16:37,148 --> 00:16:38,357
What's this?

178
00:16:38,810 --> 00:16:40,502
What are these guys over here?

179
00:16:45,627 --> 00:16:48,408
In the jeep, prisoners.
Khmer Rouge prisoners.

180
00:17:10,586 --> 00:17:12,494
They kill a lot of villagers.

181
00:17:12,859 --> 00:17:15,312
She says Khmer Rouge soak rags
in gasoline...

182
00:17:15,514 --> 00:17:17,454
...and push them down
villagers' throat...

183
00:17:17,655 --> 00:17:19,564
...then set the rags alight.

184
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:20,913
Film! No film!

185
00:17:21,112 --> 00:17:22,540
I know there's no film.

186
00:17:22,746 --> 00:17:23,824
No camera!

187
00:17:25,047 --> 00:17:26,063
No camera!

188
00:17:26,391 --> 00:17:27,537
It's all right.

189
00:17:30,393 --> 00:17:31,767
Just take it easy.

190
00:17:37,498 --> 00:17:38,992
Tell them we're jour...

191
00:17:48,278 --> 00:17:49,623
Come on! Get in!

192
00:18:31,993 --> 00:18:33,548
I'm worried.

193
00:18:34,934 --> 00:18:37,237
I'm the guy who bring you over here.

194
00:18:37,974 --> 00:18:40,113
They accuse me and they arrest me.

195
00:18:40,661 --> 00:18:43,051
How can they arrest you?
You're already arrested.

196
00:18:44,504 --> 00:18:46,409
They phone Phnom Penh about me.

197
00:18:55,381 --> 00:18:56,812
I want some cigarettes.

198
00:18:58,900 --> 00:19:00,304
And I need to take a leak.

199
00:19:03,347 --> 00:19:05,256
Would you tell them I need to piss?

200
00:19:28,436 --> 00:19:29,865
He said, "No piss."

201
00:19:31,635 --> 00:19:32,718
What does that mean?

202
00:19:33,236 --> 00:19:35,024
That's no piss.

203
00:19:39,348 --> 00:19:41,487
I've had enough of this bullshit.

204
00:19:42,133 --> 00:19:44,041
I got a story to get to New York!

205
00:19:49,074 --> 00:19:50,316
Don't leave me!

206
00:20:00,753 --> 00:20:01,967
I won't leave you.

207
00:21:07,983 --> 00:21:10,284
They brought in the whole press corps!

208
00:21:10,480 --> 00:21:13,678
They want to sanitize the story!
Bastards!

209
00:21:23,695 --> 00:21:25,736
I am going to tell you something.

210
00:21:25,969 --> 00:21:27,560
I'm walking out of here.

211
00:21:27,757 --> 00:21:29,993
What are you gonna do?
Blow my head off?

212
00:21:30,252 --> 00:21:33,124
You got a general out there,
this is an American passport...

213
00:21:33,325 --> 00:21:35,180
...and I am walking out of here!

214
00:21:37,837 --> 00:21:40,969
- He wants to get higher officer.
- Then get him! Get him!

215
00:21:49,039 --> 00:21:52,996
I'm sorry we couldn't show you the
minor bomb damage in the city itself.

216
00:21:53,196 --> 00:21:54,920
It's still a restricted area.

217
00:21:55,118 --> 00:21:57,289
Now, if you look across the river...

218
00:21:57,485 --> 00:22:00,298
...you'll see positions held by
Khmer Rouge...

219
00:22:00,493 --> 00:22:02,218
...who moved in over
the past few days.

220
00:22:02,413 --> 00:22:05,511
But the Cambodian Republican Army
is moving in on them.

221
00:22:05,710 --> 00:22:09,060
They'll have the K.R. Out
before you can say "Jack Robinson."

222
00:22:09,933 --> 00:22:11,560
Get in the chopper now!

223
00:22:11,855 --> 00:22:15,170
No, Schanberg! You came on a boat,
you go back on a boat!

224
00:22:15,372 --> 00:22:17,477
That won't stop my story!

225
00:22:20,109 --> 00:22:21,002
What is this?

226
00:22:21,196 --> 00:22:24,098
If you weren't down here,
I wouldn't be down here.

227
00:22:24,300 --> 00:22:27,083
And I don't want to be down here!
What good is it doing?

228
00:22:27,277 --> 00:22:29,033
If anybody ever reads about this...

229
00:22:29,229 --> 00:22:31,815
...you won't be able to look them
in the face!

230
00:23:10,345 --> 00:23:11,491
Good morning.

231
00:23:12,298 --> 00:23:13,249
What time is it?

232
00:23:15,145 --> 00:23:16,607
Six o'clock.

233
00:23:17,992 --> 00:23:18,855
Shit.

234
00:23:19,052 --> 00:23:20,228
Telex for you.

235
00:23:20,844 --> 00:23:22,251
You been to the telex?

236
00:23:24,554 --> 00:23:25,863
We made the front page.

237
00:23:26,059 --> 00:23:26,986
Sure.

238
00:23:29,002 --> 00:23:30,978
We must be doing something right.

239
00:23:38,633 --> 00:23:41,120
My wife is very worried.

240
00:23:41,740 --> 00:23:45,185
She thinks all foreign journalists
are going to leave Cambodia.

241
00:23:46,633 --> 00:23:48,006
Well, Pran...

242
00:23:49,163 --> 00:23:53,385
...l'd feel kind of stupid trying to
cover this war from a desk in Bangkok.

243
00:23:54,761 --> 00:23:57,726
And she said if the war
keeps going like this...

244
00:23:57,926 --> 00:23:59,999
...the future could be very bad.

245
00:24:01,800 --> 00:24:03,043
What do you think?

246
00:24:05,993 --> 00:24:07,269
I don't know.

247
00:24:09,672 --> 00:24:10,982
I don't know either.

248
00:24:13,642 --> 00:24:15,529
- Is Sarun downstairs?
- Sure.

249
00:24:16,714 --> 00:24:18,057
Let's get going.

250
00:24:18,987 --> 00:24:19,915
All right.

251
00:24:25,928 --> 00:24:27,170
Don't go back to sleep.

252
00:24:27,368 --> 00:24:28,413
I won't.

253
00:24:37,033 --> 00:24:39,171
K.R.'s making a push
for the airport road.

254
00:24:39,368 --> 00:24:41,311
If they cut it,
the city could be lost.

255
00:24:41,512 --> 00:24:44,809
We hype these people up. "You'll be
all right with us," we say.

256
00:24:44,999 --> 00:24:47,169
Now look at all this fucking mess!

257
00:24:54,088 --> 00:24:57,185
In America, everybody got a good car.

258
00:24:59,337 --> 00:25:01,605
He ask you what car you drive
in United States.

259
00:25:01,799 --> 00:25:04,733
I don't have a car in America,
only the Mercedes here.

260
00:25:04,935 --> 00:25:07,039
Mercedes, number one!

261
00:25:07,559 --> 00:25:09,980
Ask him where he learned
to speak his English.

262
00:25:12,836 --> 00:25:15,203
American advisor with his unit
teach him.

263
00:25:15,398 --> 00:25:17,372
Mercedes, number one, okay?

264
00:25:54,087 --> 00:25:55,099
What did he say?

265
00:25:55,300 --> 00:25:58,203
He said he thought all
American people left already.

266
00:25:58,824 --> 00:26:00,676
Made in the USA.

267
00:26:04,035 --> 00:26:05,016
Are we winning?

268
00:26:05,892 --> 00:26:07,898
No, you're not winning.

269
00:26:08,100 --> 00:26:09,376
What should we do?

270
00:26:09,569 --> 00:26:12,669
Well, you make sure they don't
cut off the airport road.

271
00:26:15,524 --> 00:26:17,759
The first section came
by Route number 36.

272
00:26:18,404 --> 00:26:21,948
And the second one
came down by Route number 26.

273
00:26:22,148 --> 00:26:24,538
Khmer Rouge will come down Route 3.

274
00:26:24,964 --> 00:26:26,339
He doesn't know how many.

275
00:26:26,531 --> 00:26:28,440
They expect an attack today.

276
00:26:28,642 --> 00:26:30,071
- Where's your commander?
- Phnom Penh.

277
00:26:30,274 --> 00:26:31,617
- Why there?
- Don't know.

278
00:26:31,811 --> 00:26:33,666
How many mortar rounds you have...?

279
00:26:47,492 --> 00:26:50,940
Rockoff, get your ass out here!
Get out here!

280
00:26:53,473 --> 00:26:55,644
Come on, let's get him out of here!

281
00:27:22,209 --> 00:27:23,485
- Fuck this!
- They pulling out?

282
00:27:23,681 --> 00:27:25,535
I'm not happy here, Syd.

283
00:27:25,730 --> 00:27:27,552
Jon, I'm leaving.

284
00:27:27,811 --> 00:27:29,305
Syd, come on!

285
00:27:29,632 --> 00:27:30,581
Come on!

286
00:27:43,615 --> 00:27:45,023
Sydney, this way!

287
00:28:05,471 --> 00:28:07,193
Sydney, look! Khmer Rouge!

288
00:28:54,750 --> 00:28:57,561
In Washington, the
Cambodian ambassador...

289
00:28:57,754 --> 00:29:00,537
...in a speech to
the Washington Press Club said:

290
00:29:00,734 --> 00:29:03,516
"Let's face it, you took
advantage of us."

291
00:29:03,708 --> 00:29:04,569
I can't eat.

292
00:29:04,764 --> 00:29:09,401
"You are cleverer than we are, and
you induced us into this fighting."

293
00:29:10,109 --> 00:29:13,045
Indeed, the Khmer Rouge
insurgents in Cambodia...

294
00:29:13,246 --> 00:29:16,279
...have tightened their ring
around the capital, Phnom Penh...

295
00:29:16,478 --> 00:29:19,928
...now swollen with some two million
refugees from the fighting.

296
00:29:20,126 --> 00:29:24,184
Reports from government troops talk
of the field situation being so bad...

297
00:29:24,379 --> 00:29:27,576
...that soldiers are having
to siphon gas from jeep to jeep...

298
00:29:27,774 --> 00:29:31,571
...in order to be able to get
the wounded back to the capital.

299
00:29:50,970 --> 00:29:52,693
No more electricity.

300
00:30:24,604 --> 00:30:27,122
And now I get a message
to try for negotiations.

301
00:30:27,324 --> 00:30:29,210
Well, it's just too goddamn late!

302
00:30:29,401 --> 00:30:31,640
Alan, this country's split apart.

303
00:30:31,833 --> 00:30:35,479
We put this ship to sea, and it breaks
my heart not to help it back to port.

304
00:30:35,675 --> 00:30:36,723
Any port.

305
00:30:37,846 --> 00:30:41,494
What pisses me off is, this country
has faults and strengths...

306
00:30:41,688 --> 00:30:45,103
...and we have done nothing
but play to the faults.

307
00:30:47,703 --> 00:30:50,575
I tell you, I will be damn
glad to get out of here.

308
00:30:50,778 --> 00:30:55,316
This thing has dragged on too long for
it to end in all sweetness and light.

309
00:30:55,513 --> 00:30:57,686
After what the Khmer Rouge
have been through...

310
00:30:57,883 --> 00:31:00,728
...they won't be exactly
affectionate toward Westerners.

311
00:31:02,774 --> 00:31:05,590
- Where do you want this?
- On the floor. Anywhere.

312
00:31:05,784 --> 00:31:09,232
- Mr. Schanberg...
- Oh, Christ, my dependents! Six.

313
00:31:09,432 --> 00:31:10,643
Dith Pran and family.

314
00:31:10,840 --> 00:31:11,823
Right.

315
00:31:13,112 --> 00:31:17,750
"Dear sir, my family and I are planning
a touring vacation of Southeast Asia...

316
00:31:17,944 --> 00:31:22,483
...and anticipate two weeks
in Cambodia touring the country.

317
00:31:23,096 --> 00:31:26,293
Would you please send tour
information and brochures?

318
00:31:26,489 --> 00:31:28,690
Thanking you in advance,
Wendell Payne."

319
00:31:28,886 --> 00:31:31,666
Wendell lives in Wisacky,
South Carolina.

320
00:31:32,789 --> 00:31:33,903
What about the airlift?

321
00:31:34,103 --> 00:31:35,598
We're taking it with us.

322
00:31:36,441 --> 00:31:39,637
- People will starve to death.
- I know, but what can we do?

323
00:31:39,831 --> 00:31:42,101
Look, there could be a bloodbath here.

324
00:31:43,352 --> 00:31:46,963
Excuse the pun, but we're
either staying or we're living.

325
00:31:57,974 --> 00:32:01,292
Hello, leaving a sinking ship then,
are we, Carver?

326
00:32:06,166 --> 00:32:10,357
President Ford, in his foreign policy
speech, hardly referred to Cambodia...

327
00:32:10,551 --> 00:32:14,325
...except to say that, as of now,
it may be too late.

328
00:32:29,109 --> 00:32:30,604
I'm sorry. I'm late.

329
00:32:30,806 --> 00:32:32,014
Where you been?

330
00:32:32,342 --> 00:32:34,958
- They stop me because of the curfew.
- The curfew, huh?

331
00:32:35,158 --> 00:32:36,717
Yes. I'm sorry.

332
00:32:39,158 --> 00:32:42,471
Get started on this.
Tell them to start sending this out...

333
00:32:42,677 --> 00:32:46,223
...but hold the last two paragraphs.
I'll have corrections in an hour.

334
00:32:47,411 --> 00:32:51,244
They don't transmit today.
The transmitter at Kambol got hit.

335
00:32:52,852 --> 00:32:55,119
They say 6 p.m. We can file.

336
00:32:55,315 --> 00:32:56,689
6 p.m.

337
00:32:58,261 --> 00:33:01,491
What do you think this is?
A monthly magazine?

338
00:33:01,684 --> 00:33:03,594
This is a newspaper.

339
00:33:06,453 --> 00:33:08,109
How about update tomorrow?

340
00:33:10,772 --> 00:33:13,521
Yeah, sure. We can file
an update tomorrow.

341
00:33:22,612 --> 00:33:24,914
I was over at the
American Embassy yesterday.

342
00:33:26,100 --> 00:33:26,930
Good news?

343
00:33:27,126 --> 00:33:28,849
No, not good news.

344
00:33:34,611 --> 00:33:37,229
They say that when
this place goes up...

345
00:33:40,498 --> 00:33:43,948
...they think a lot of people
will be killed. A lot of people.

346
00:33:45,137 --> 00:33:48,652
I've arranged for the evacuation
of you and your family.

347
00:33:51,381 --> 00:33:53,714
So now it's up to you.
What do you want to do?

348
00:33:56,116 --> 00:33:58,054
Do you want to stay
or leave?

349
00:34:06,418 --> 00:34:07,397
And how about you?

350
00:34:08,563 --> 00:34:10,351
That's none of your business.

351
00:34:16,049 --> 00:34:18,671
Do you want to stay,
or do you want to leave?

352
00:34:22,098 --> 00:34:23,241
I know.

353
00:34:23,983 --> 00:34:25,544
You love my family.

354
00:34:29,649 --> 00:34:32,430
But me, I'm reporter too.

355
00:34:33,104 --> 00:34:34,535
You know what I mean?

356
00:34:49,102 --> 00:34:52,614
All right, we don't have
to decide this right now.

357
00:34:52,815 --> 00:34:54,123
Take it easy.

358
00:34:58,958 --> 00:35:01,926
But we'll have to make up our
minds pretty soon, right?

359
00:36:11,852 --> 00:36:14,439
All right, this is it!
Is the floor clear?

360
00:36:15,659 --> 00:36:17,286
This is the last check.

361
00:36:20,045 --> 00:36:22,499
Last check. This is the last check!

362
00:36:28,841 --> 00:36:30,271
Mr. Kincaid is not here.

363
00:36:30,571 --> 00:36:33,506
Mr. Kincaid is gone.
You keep Mr. Kincaid's money.

364
00:36:33,930 --> 00:36:35,654
Now, I want you to go right now!

365
00:36:36,076 --> 00:36:37,601
I want you to leave now!

366
00:36:37,802 --> 00:36:39,811
You won't see Mr. Kincaid again!

367
00:36:52,713 --> 00:36:54,819
Okay, sergeant, let him in!

368
00:36:57,866 --> 00:37:01,032
Have you got Pran here?
Have you got Pran on there?

369
00:37:01,227 --> 00:37:03,748
- And his wife?
- Yes, sir, they are.

370
00:37:03,946 --> 00:37:07,046
- Did they come in yet?
- No, sir, they haven't arrived yet.

371
00:37:19,690 --> 00:37:21,380
Have you seen Pran?

372
00:37:21,575 --> 00:37:22,526
No, I haven't.

373
00:37:23,273 --> 00:37:24,255
Where is he?

374
00:37:28,105 --> 00:37:29,828
Well, it's been real.

375
00:37:35,113 --> 00:37:36,543
They're gonna miss it.

376
00:37:37,287 --> 00:37:39,712
Why don't you check around
the other side?

377
00:37:40,361 --> 00:37:43,262
If he comes here, I'm looking
for him in the back.

378
00:37:54,887 --> 00:37:57,221
Beth! Have you seen Pran?

379
00:37:57,416 --> 00:37:59,522
No, have you looked at the hotel?

380
00:37:59,719 --> 00:38:01,508
He's at the post office!

381
00:38:01,897 --> 00:38:03,423
The post office!

382
00:38:30,921 --> 00:38:33,089
Get the fuck out!
Get out of here now!

383
00:38:33,351 --> 00:38:35,454
Move your asses out of here!

384
00:38:35,911 --> 00:38:37,317
Hold those doors!

385
00:38:41,128 --> 00:38:43,942
- Where do you think you're going?
- To embassy.

386
00:38:59,173 --> 00:39:00,603
Yes, sir, what's your name?

387
00:39:00,805 --> 00:39:02,115
Dith Pran family, sir.

388
00:39:02,308 --> 00:39:03,999
Dith Pran family?

389
00:39:04,197 --> 00:39:06,434
- Sydney Schanberg.
- They've been through.

390
00:39:06,884 --> 00:39:09,274
- They've been through.
- Check one more time, please.

391
00:39:09,477 --> 00:39:11,649
- You made a mistake, sir.
- No mistake.

392
00:39:19,750 --> 00:39:21,158
Rockoff, help me!

393
00:41:28,064 --> 00:41:28,859
Run!

394
00:41:29,311 --> 00:41:30,741
There's no time!

395
00:42:36,511 --> 00:42:37,438
Wait a minute.

396
00:42:40,991 --> 00:42:41,972
Smile.

397
00:43:07,801 --> 00:43:08,817
Jon.

398
00:43:09,371 --> 00:43:10,418
Hello, Sydney.

399
00:43:27,132 --> 00:43:30,875
If the going gets rough, I heard
our best bet's the French Embassy.

400
00:43:33,531 --> 00:43:34,775
Who told you that?

401
00:43:37,625 --> 00:43:39,285
The British Embassy.

402
00:44:08,537 --> 00:44:10,130
Khmer Rouge coming.

403
00:44:10,330 --> 00:44:13,366
Look like government soldiers
give them big welcome.

404
00:45:15,062 --> 00:45:16,404
No more fighting!

405
00:45:16,759 --> 00:45:18,035
I be right back!

406
00:45:33,527 --> 00:45:35,284
No more fighting! No more war!

407
00:45:35,703 --> 00:45:36,979
What do you think?

408
00:45:38,038 --> 00:45:39,695
I don't like the look of this.

409
00:45:39,894 --> 00:45:44,401
I was in Keng Kang this morning.
Practically got my ass shot off.

410
00:45:44,597 --> 00:45:47,412
I just don't think these guys
are for real.

411
00:45:47,670 --> 00:45:50,737
I'm going to the hospital.
You want to come with me?

412
00:46:55,410 --> 00:46:57,682
Tetracaine, 50 milligrams, please.

413
00:46:58,482 --> 00:47:01,101
Jesus, what am I supposed to do?
Sing her a lullaby?

414
00:47:01,301 --> 00:47:03,570
Pentothal, 150 milligrams, quick.

415
00:47:14,452 --> 00:47:17,613
Jesus, another shrapnel
in the spine here.

416
00:47:17,808 --> 00:47:19,435
Okay, let's have her over.

417
00:47:25,009 --> 00:47:29,417
This is blood group A. We've had one
unit of blood in the last two days.

418
00:47:30,290 --> 00:47:32,232
Plasma substitute, please, quick.

419
00:47:33,107 --> 00:47:35,595
We've plenty of blood, gentlemen.
Plenty of blood.

420
00:47:35,794 --> 00:47:38,282
The problem is, it's all in
the wrong fucking place.

421
00:47:41,011 --> 00:47:45,003
Why do corpses have to pile up before
people decide it's time to go home?

422
00:48:11,696 --> 00:48:14,118
For God's sake, back up the car!
Sarun, back it up!

423
00:48:14,321 --> 00:48:16,654
For God's sake, back it up now!

424
00:49:29,293 --> 00:49:32,676
- Why doesn't he get his ass in here?
- He's trying to get in!

425
00:49:33,165 --> 00:49:34,408
They won't let him in.

426
00:49:57,036 --> 00:49:58,116
All right?

427
00:56:01,471 --> 00:56:02,362
Okay?

428
00:56:02,556 --> 00:56:03,703
Looks all right.

429
00:58:56,728 --> 00:58:57,741
I'm coming!

430
00:59:05,335 --> 00:59:07,277
Just a minute! He's with me!

431
00:59:07,543 --> 00:59:09,299
He's with The New York Times!

432
00:59:09,495 --> 00:59:12,561
Wait just a minute!
He's a journalist and he's with me!

433
00:59:13,113 --> 00:59:16,373
Where is the consul? I want to talk
to the consul. Let me see him!

434
00:59:16,630 --> 00:59:19,184
You tell me where he is.
I want to speak to him!

435
00:59:20,120 --> 00:59:23,795
The picture in Cambodia
is increasingly unclear.

436
00:59:23,991 --> 00:59:27,253
Journalists who have flown
from Thailand over Phnom Penh...

437
00:59:27,445 --> 00:59:29,998
...report that the Khmer Rouge
have attempted...

438
00:59:30,197 --> 00:59:33,198
...a mass evacuation
of the entire population.

439
00:59:33,398 --> 00:59:37,773
Radio contact with the French Embassy
reveals that some 200 Europeans...

440
00:59:37,973 --> 00:59:42,099
...and an undisclosed number
of Cambodians have taken refuge.

441
00:59:42,293 --> 00:59:46,257
As yet, no statement has been made
by the new rulers of Cambodia.

442
00:59:46,456 --> 00:59:50,828
The whereabouts of Prince Sihanouk
and the Khmer Rouge leadership...

443
00:59:51,028 --> 00:59:52,434
...are not clear.

444
00:59:58,101 --> 01:00:00,433
- Okay?
- Yes. He's sleeping.

445
01:00:25,171 --> 01:00:26,000
That's the consul.

446
01:00:34,901 --> 01:00:37,713
- Did you see that, Dennis?
- The Russians are coming.

447
01:00:43,698 --> 01:00:45,390
Look, piss off! Please!

448
01:00:45,587 --> 01:00:48,588
Get out! You won't get
anything here! Out!

449
01:00:56,019 --> 01:00:57,931
First, the main points of the news.

450
01:00:58,131 --> 01:00:59,592
BBC, Dougal.

451
01:01:02,226 --> 01:01:04,943
- Daily reports of fighting
around the airport...

452
01:01:05,137 --> 01:01:08,815
...14 kilometers outside Phnom Penh,
the capital of Cambodia.

453
01:01:09,714 --> 01:01:13,488
And now, an on-the-spot report
from our correspondent in Thailand...

454
01:01:13,683 --> 01:01:14,697
...Hugh Elder.

455
01:01:16,561 --> 01:01:18,603
Where do they get this crap?

456
01:01:19,122 --> 01:01:22,122
Do you see that guy across the gate?
The little guy?

457
01:01:23,187 --> 01:01:25,607
Could we not all look at once, please?

458
01:01:26,355 --> 01:01:29,799
I have it on reliable sources
that that's Hugh Elder.

459
01:01:30,512 --> 01:01:31,309
You're kidding.

460
01:01:31,504 --> 01:01:34,821
He's disguised, but I got suspicious
about him. You know what I mean?

461
01:01:35,023 --> 01:01:37,871
- How does he get copy out?
- How does he get his copy out?

462
01:01:38,066 --> 01:01:39,723
With specially trained hens.

463
01:01:40,977 --> 01:01:45,004
The BBC has, like, commissioned
them to walk past the Khmer Rouge...

464
01:01:45,201 --> 01:01:46,892
...like their regular fowl.

465
01:01:47,090 --> 01:01:51,433
They've been crossing the border into
Thailand every day and every night.

466
01:01:52,464 --> 01:01:53,479
I told you.

467
01:01:54,320 --> 01:01:57,451
Unconfirmed reports say
the Khmer Rouge are demanding...

468
01:01:57,647 --> 01:02:01,128
...that any officials of
the defeated Lon Nol government...

469
01:02:01,330 --> 01:02:04,296
...especially the so-called
Six Traitors of the Cabinet...

470
01:02:04,497 --> 01:02:06,057
...be handed over to them.

471
01:02:06,256 --> 01:02:08,875
It is not known whether
any of the ex-ministers...

472
01:02:09,071 --> 01:02:11,079
...may have taken refuge
in the embassy...

473
01:02:11,282 --> 01:02:14,576
...where, in the words of a UNICEF
representative in Bangkok...

474
01:02:14,769 --> 01:02:18,543
...the situation is said to be
"increasingly precarious."

475
01:03:44,253 --> 01:03:47,831
And when I tried to go
just a kilometer further, no.

476
01:03:48,030 --> 01:03:50,550
The only sense I can make of it
is that there's...

477
01:03:50,751 --> 01:03:53,567
...some sort of internal
power struggle going on.

478
01:03:54,112 --> 01:03:57,369
Different groups seem to be
holding different parts of the city...

479
01:03:58,047 --> 01:04:02,651
...and they all appear to be equally
nervous over losing power and control.

480
01:04:03,199 --> 01:04:05,139
Half of them are under 15.

481
01:04:05,822 --> 01:04:08,638
Some Red Cross instruction
sheets want translating.

482
01:04:08,832 --> 01:04:09,781
Can you help?

483
01:04:10,112 --> 01:04:12,447
Use Pran. He speaks French
better than I do.

484
01:04:12,640 --> 01:04:14,615
I'd prefer it if it was you.

485
01:04:25,471 --> 01:04:26,901
What did you do that for?

486
01:04:27,328 --> 01:04:29,400
The guy's insecure enough already.

487
01:04:31,584 --> 01:04:34,007
The Cambodians have
to leave the embassy.

488
01:04:36,608 --> 01:04:40,022
They want all our passports
and everybody downstairs...

489
01:04:40,513 --> 01:04:42,487
...and the Cambodians out.

490
01:05:18,948 --> 01:05:20,672
If you have papers,
you have a name.

491
01:05:20,868 --> 01:05:22,974
If we have a name,
we can find the mother.

492
01:05:23,717 --> 01:05:26,237
Look, I fight for five years.

493
01:05:26,853 --> 01:05:28,162
Useless war.

494
01:05:31,416 --> 01:05:32,166
Fuck!

495
01:05:34,765 --> 01:05:37,417
You know, Pran is not gonna last
five minutes out there.

496
01:05:37,612 --> 01:05:41,222
The Khmer Rouge have killed every
