750
01:45:35,310 --> 01:45:38,089
- That was great, really good.
- Better than last year.

751
01:45:38,953 --> 01:45:41,408
Abe, meet my sister.

752
01:45:41,610 --> 01:45:43,365
I'm very happy to meet you.

753
01:45:43,561 --> 01:45:45,929
That's my dad.
Would you hold this for me?

754
01:45:46,986 --> 01:45:47,916
One second.

755
01:45:48,107 --> 01:45:51,174
I hoped you could recommend
a good school for journalism.

756
01:45:51,372 --> 01:45:54,221
I told my daughter I'd be
seeing you today.

757
01:45:54,413 --> 01:45:57,165
Just one minute, okay?
I'll be right back.

758
01:46:05,931 --> 01:46:09,577
Could I have your autograph?
I'm a great admirer of yours.

759
01:46:12,077 --> 01:46:14,664
Congratulations on your award,
it was well-deserved.

760
01:46:14,862 --> 01:46:17,994
Very impressive.
I was hoping you'd burst into song.

761
01:46:19,406 --> 01:46:22,025
- What are you doing here?
- You know what bothers me?

762
01:46:22,223 --> 01:46:23,019
What?

763
01:46:23,407 --> 01:46:25,992
It bothers me that you let Pran
stay in Cambodia...

764
01:46:26,189 --> 01:46:29,188
...because you wanted to win,
and you knew you needed him...

765
01:46:29,389 --> 01:46:32,007
- I didn't have any idea what...
- The fuck you didn't!

766
01:46:33,836 --> 01:46:35,876
The fuck you didn't.

767
01:46:36,460 --> 01:46:39,814
I did everything I could,
and I'm doing everything I can.

768
01:46:40,016 --> 01:46:42,253
Nice to see you.
I'm on my way to Florida.

769
01:46:42,448 --> 01:46:43,942
I'm doing everything I can.

770
01:46:44,142 --> 01:46:47,309
I'm sure. I didn't realize
you'd been out there to see him.

771
01:46:47,507 --> 01:46:50,637
Don't play games with me, Al.
Don't play stupid games.

772
01:46:50,831 --> 01:46:54,345
Nobody gets to go in there.
If I thought I could, I would.

773
01:46:55,183 --> 01:46:57,127
I've sent out hundreds of photographs.

774
01:46:57,328 --> 01:47:00,839
Every relief organization
on the Thai-Kampuchean border...

775
01:47:04,400 --> 01:47:08,045
...has got his picture. If I saw
one glimmer of hope, I'd go today.

776
01:47:08,560 --> 01:47:10,023
Life isn't a '40s movie.

777
01:47:10,224 --> 01:47:13,903
You can't just get on a plane and
make the whole world come out right!

778
01:47:15,443 --> 01:47:18,125
And I can't believe
I'm hearing this from you!

779
01:47:22,737 --> 01:47:23,977
Congrats.

780
01:47:25,967 --> 01:47:28,424
Do you keep in touch
with Dith Pran's family?

781
01:47:28,622 --> 01:47:30,731
Yes. They're living in San Francisco.

782
01:47:30,929 --> 01:47:33,678
How do you respond to accusations
that journalists...

783
01:47:33,874 --> 01:47:36,142
...underestimated the brutality
of the Khmer Rouge...

784
01:47:36,338 --> 01:47:39,919
...and so share responsibility for
what happened in Cambodia afterwards?

785
01:47:40,566 --> 01:47:42,320
We made a mistake.

786
01:47:42,866 --> 01:47:45,355
Maybe we underestimated
the kind of insanity...

787
01:47:45,553 --> 01:47:47,977
...that $ 7 billion worth
of bombing could produce.

788
01:47:48,177 --> 01:47:49,292
That is provocative...

789
01:47:49,490 --> 01:47:52,751
There have been a lot of refugee
stories in Reader's Digest...

790
01:47:52,947 --> 01:47:55,283
...about Cambodia.
Do you believe them?

791
01:47:55,473 --> 01:47:56,971
Don't you believe them?

792
01:47:57,171 --> 01:48:00,881
Maybe in this instance the
Reader's Digest happens to be correct.

793
01:48:01,076 --> 01:48:03,278
Do you apply the same disbelief
to stories...

794
01:48:03,476 --> 01:48:05,865
...that come out of Iran
or Palestine or Chile?

795
01:48:06,069 --> 01:48:08,335
Are refugees your next area
of interest?

796
01:48:08,530 --> 01:48:10,865
Will you be covering the boat people?

797
01:48:11,057 --> 01:48:12,137
No, I will not.

798
01:48:12,339 --> 01:48:13,964
Do you want a cup of tea?

799
01:48:14,899 --> 01:48:18,348
Are you looking around for some kind
of more salable suffering?

800
01:48:20,820 --> 01:48:23,342
I must have sent 500 letters.

801
01:48:28,628 --> 01:48:32,208
I wrote the International Red Cross,
the World Health Organization.

802
01:48:32,406 --> 01:48:34,991
I know you did, Syd.
You told me.

803
01:48:35,477 --> 01:48:37,650
I don't know who I didn't write to.

804
01:48:43,862 --> 01:48:46,413
I never really gave him any choice.

805
01:48:51,639 --> 01:48:54,640
One time we tried to discuss leaving.

806
01:49:03,221 --> 01:49:06,540
I talked to him about it,
but we never really discussed it.

807
01:49:09,718 --> 01:49:12,884
I discussed it with Swain and Rockoff.

808
01:49:16,728 --> 01:49:19,150
But I never discussed it with him.

809
01:49:29,880 --> 01:49:32,697
He stayed because
I wanted him to stay.

810
01:49:38,488 --> 01:49:40,277
And I stayed because...

811
01:53:10,723 --> 01:53:12,513
I'm trapped, Sydney.

812
01:53:12,710 --> 01:53:16,733
I know he suspects me,
and yet he treats me well.

813
01:53:17,347 --> 01:53:20,608
There are many different groups
over here, Sydney.

814
01:53:20,900 --> 01:53:22,908
I must take much care.

815
01:53:23,429 --> 01:53:27,326
Now Angka says we have new enemies.

816
01:53:27,847 --> 01:53:32,549
They say we must regain
our old lands from the Vietnamese.

817
01:53:33,283 --> 01:53:37,027
And now they say we must fight them.

818
01:53:38,757 --> 01:53:42,784
I miss you, my wife, my children.

819
01:53:42,981 --> 01:53:46,296
And my heart hungers for news of you.

820
01:54:09,448 --> 01:54:10,910
New China Radio reports...

821
01:54:11,111 --> 01:54:14,277
...that fighting between Vietnam
and Democratic Kampuchea...

822
01:54:14,472 --> 01:54:16,741
...has broken out
on a number of fronts.

823
01:54:17,001 --> 01:54:19,619
This is in retaliation,
according to the Vietnamese...

824
01:54:19,818 --> 01:54:22,150
...for a number of attacks
on border villages...

825
01:54:25,734 --> 01:54:27,044
Taxi driver, huh?

826
01:54:44,170 --> 01:54:45,925
I think you speak English.

827
01:54:46,376 --> 01:54:47,618
Sit down.

828
01:54:53,577 --> 01:54:55,999
You know, I love this country.

829
01:54:57,737 --> 01:55:00,421
I sacrificed everything for it.

830
01:55:01,835 --> 01:55:05,185
My wife died for the revolution.

831
01:55:07,019 --> 01:55:11,525
But the leaders of Angka
no longer trust the people.

832
01:55:12,427 --> 01:55:15,843
Therefore, I can no longer trust them.

833
01:55:17,611 --> 01:55:19,585
And they don't trust me.

834
01:55:21,996 --> 01:55:22,825
I fear...

835
01:55:24,171 --> 01:55:26,408
...really fear for the future.

836
01:55:30,635 --> 01:55:33,986
I think you love my son.

837
01:55:36,975 --> 01:55:38,179
For his sake...

838
01:55:39,210 --> 01:55:40,551
...look after him.

839
01:55:45,005 --> 01:55:47,491
The fighting is close by, Sydney.

840
01:55:47,691 --> 01:55:50,058
If the Vietnamese get here...

841
01:55:50,252 --> 01:55:52,327
...Angka will destroy everything...

842
01:55:54,382 --> 01:55:55,877
...and the Vietnamese,
they will find only ashes.

843
01:58:57,462 --> 01:59:00,756
I must try to stop the killing.
Good luck.

844
02:07:57,237 --> 02:07:59,059
Yeah, I'll be right there, Brian.

845
02:08:01,876 --> 02:08:05,674
Ann, get me 415-555-6421.

846
02:08:05,877 --> 02:08:07,502
Abe, I've got some great news!

847
02:08:20,180 --> 02:08:23,116
Twenty minutes ago, I get
a phone call from Paris.

848
02:08:23,318 --> 02:08:26,101
I get Andreas Freund.
He talked to Henry.

849
02:08:26,296 --> 02:08:28,302
He told him how to get in touch
with me.

850
02:08:28,503 --> 02:08:31,253
Freund says, "I have got
some great news for you."

851
02:08:31,449 --> 02:08:33,965
- San Francisco's on the line.
- "It's about Pran!"

852
02:08:34,325 --> 02:08:35,951
Is your mother there?

853
02:08:38,455 --> 02:08:39,566
When?

854
02:08:41,879 --> 02:08:44,434
All right,
I want you to get this down.

855
02:08:45,240 --> 02:08:47,793
No, write it down. Write it down.

856
02:08:49,273 --> 02:08:51,311
I've got a message from your dad!

857
02:10:01,274 --> 02:10:02,421
How you been?

858
02:10:14,971 --> 02:10:15,953
Do you forgive me?

859
02:10:16,635 --> 02:10:19,124
Nothing to forgive, Sydney.
Nothing.